Chelsea boss, Frank Lampard, has provided the latest update on Kai Havertz, Thiago Silva and Christian Pulisic ahead of his side’s Champions League clash against Rennes on Tuesday evening in France. Lampard’s men head to the game following a 2-0 victory over Newcastle United in the Premier League on Saturday. Providing an update on Havertz, Silva and Pulisic, Lampard told a pre-match press conference on Monday that, “Kai and Thiago, both travelled and are fit for selection. “Christian stays back and doesn’t travel but the good news is that he has had good progression in the last week. “The reason he is staying back is to get some physical work in to have him ready for selection for this weekend hopefully and onwards.” Match kick-off time for Rennes vs Chelsea fixture is 6:55 pm.